tspan.tspan: Setup
To get you started we need to go through a few steps that take a few minutes
to
complete...
First off we need to get you connected using a 'cypto wallet' that will
permanently identify you and your data.
You can create your new personalized wallet by clicking 'Create My Wallet'
below.
Once you've downloaded your wallet file, back it up onto a USB memory stick or
another offline storage device for safe keeping.
Click 'next' to continue.
Connect your wallet
Now that your wallet is downloaded, you need to tell Evermore where you saved
it on your computer.
After that, select a folder on your system where you want to place files that you
are going to save to the blockchain.
We recommend you create an 'Evermore' folder in your Documents folder, but
its possible to select any folder that you choose
Click 'Connect' to proceed.
All Done!
Your all set to begin saving your data premanently on the blockchain!
If you need any help at anytime please feel free to checkout our FAQs and
Video
tutorials available online at https://www.evermoredata.store
Click 'Connect' to proceed.
Selective File Sync
Setup has detected you already have files in the folder you selected.
You can tell Evermore which of those files to save and which ones to ignore
using the next dialog.
Simply click save on the next dialog to include all the files setup found or
uncheck the ones you want ignored.
Click 'Configure Selective Files Sync' to proceed.
